      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:5:2:14",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ مَنَعَ قِيرَاطاً مِنَ الزَّكَاةِ فَلْيَمُتْ إِنْ شَاءَ يَهُودِيّاً أَوْ نَصْرَانِيّاً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Ali Al Ashary, from the one who mentioned it, from Hafs Bin Umar, from Salim, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who prevents a carat of <span class=\"iTxt\">Zakāt</span>, so let him die, if he so desires to as a Jew, or a Christian’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "14. Abu Ali al-Ash’ariy has narrated from those whom he has mentioned from Hafs ibn ‘Umar from Salim from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that one (Muslim) who does not pay zakat dies as a Jew or a Christian; (he is given the chance to choose).” "
        ]
      }
    },
